Finished! After over a month and close to 100 hours of work I’ve finished one of my biggest projects to date. I don’t know if this is the best that I can do, but it’s as close as I’m willing to get for now haha. Thank you to all of you who followed the entire project and left your comments and feedback.

Hello everyone! I am now offering subscriptions on Instagram but I would like to explain why - I joined this hobby in 2020 in order to have some fun during the lockdowns. 3 years later I am somehow approaching 40K followers (appropriate number lol). This has always been just a fun hobby to me and I hope it will always remain that way. 
.
I’m not a polished YouTuber or influencer gaming the algorithm, I simply post high quality photos of whatever mini I am currently painting and all of you seem to have appreciated that over the years. With that said, the hobby is getting quite expensive. A subscription to my channel is really just helping me continue to buy, paint, and post my work regularly. 
.
I’ll keep posting my high quality photos to the main feed, but I envision more casual updates of my work bench, paint recipes, coaching tips, etc to appear for my subscribers. You would be helping me afford the hobby so I would like to help you achieve your painting goals. Thank you to all of you who have supported me to 40K followers. 
.
.
.
.
